\subsection{Modification of the fractional cell kill law}

In \cite{validbul}, the particular nature of the function $h(T)$ appearing in Eq.~\eqref{eq:7} was also discussed, proving that if instead of $h(T)=s T^{\lambda}$, $h(T)=s T^{\lambda+\Delta \lambda}$ is used, the empirical results can also be validated by simply decreasing the value of $s$, even for values $\Delta \lambda/\lambda$ greater that one. This means that the original proposal of a saturating fractional cell kill depending on the quotient $E/T$ can not be guaranteed. 
